Support for automake added:
(Ready made packages will have configure, so first 4 steps aren't necessary)
aclocal
autoconf
automake -a
./configure

make

caracad should be run via init-script. The socket it is listening is:

srwxr-xr-x    1 skr      users           0 Aug 30 13:49 /tmp/caracad=

Permissions will be preserved, so you can adjust them to your needs.




REQUIREMENTS for gcanterm:(what I use but older versions may well work)


Package     my version	available from
-------     ----------  --------------
Glade       0.5.5       http://glade.pn.org/
Glib/Gtk+   1.2.7       ftp://ftp.gimp.org/pub/gtk/
gnome-libs  1.0.58      Gnome mirrors or Gnome.org CVS 
Perl-Gtk    0.7002      CPAN 
Perl        5.005_03    CPAN
XML::Parser 2.27        CPAN

all of the above are part of Debian 2.2
Glade::PerlGenerate     Gtk-Perl-Glade UI builder and source generator
http://freespace.virgin.net/dermot.musgrove/computers/perl/
or http://www.glade.perl.connectfree.co.uk/index.html
or on CPAN under the Glade module,
e.g. ftp://sunsite.doc.ic.ac.uk/packages/CPAN/modules/by-module/Glade/


